  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis is a feature request to add an `--exit-epoch` flag to the `lighthouse account validator exit` command.\r\n\r\nThis feature allows the user to set a specific epoch for the voluntary exit. It is supported by other validator clients such as [teku](https://docs.teku.consensys.net/reference/cli/subcommands/voluntary-exit#epoch), [lodestar](https://chainsafe.github.io/lodestar/reference/cli/#validator-voluntary-exit) and [nimbus](https://nimbus.guide/voluntary-exit.html).\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nNone.\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nCurrently, a user can't specify the desired epoch to exit and the lighthouse VC broadcasts exit message with the current epoch.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe validator client should allow a user to set a desired exit epoch.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n* Add a new flag `--exit-epoch` to https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/stable/account_manager/src/validator/exit.rs. \r\n* Modify `publish_voluntary_exit()` [function](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/stable/account_manager/src/validator/exit.rs#L148) to use the `epoch` provided above (if any).\r\n",
